  "text": "Our in vivo results demonstrate that a single L4F mutation in the Gla domain of mFVIIa can enhance its hemostatic capacity in HB mice. Moreover, mFVIIa-L4F's pharmacokinetics and enhanced hemostatic properties and their EPCR dependency versus mFVIIa were comparable to previous observations made with mFVIIa-FMR [CITATION_1] . Therefore, our data uniformly suggest that the L4F modification is solely responsible for the EPCRdependent enhanced hemostatic effects that we previously observed with the triple mutant mFVIIa-FMR [CITATION_2] .",
